    <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><b>Project Title:</b> ShopEZ - Vintage Sepia Neubrutalist E-Commerce Platform</li>
        <li><b>Team Members:</b> Full Stack Development Team</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. Project Overview</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><b>Purpose:</b> Provide a nostalgic, pleasant, and premium shopping portal for retro-tech collectors, eliminating corporate flat layouts.</li>
        <li><b>Key Features:</b> Shimmering skeletons, advanced sorting filters, 3D flipping card checkouts, and clean seller metrics.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Architecture</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><b>Frontend:</b> Single Page App (SPA) built with React.js using hooks, context providers, custom toast managers, and Bootstrap grids.</li>
        <li><b>Backend:</b> Node.js & Express.js with custom asyncHandler wrapping, route validations, and JSON controllers.</li>
        <li><b>Database:</b> MongoDB document schema managing orders, users, and product catalogs.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Setup Instructions</h2>
    <p>Please refer to the repository <span class="highlight">README.md</span> for the latest installation commands, ENV configurations, and seeding guidelines.</p>

    <h2>5. Running the Application</h2>
    <p>Run the local backend server via <span class="highlight">npm start</span> under `backend/` and frontend dev server via <span class="highlight">npm start</span> under `frontend/`.</p>

    <h2>6. Authentication & Security</h2>
    <p>Passwords are hashed using Bcrypt. Routes are guarded with JWT verifiers. Stale sessions are managed via global Axios response interceptors.</p>
    
